16:47.407 --> 16:48.673
- No, not really.

16:48.775 --> 16:50.241
- Oh.

16:50.276 --> 16:52.543
- She's had a little bit
of a hard time, you know.

16:52.579 --> 16:54.345
That's partly my fault.

16:54.381 --> 16:55.913
- Oh, well.

16:55.949 --> 16:57.148
- But she loves your class.

16:57.283 --> 16:59.117
- Oh, I'm so glad to hear that.

16:59.219 --> 17:00.651
- Yeah, me too.

17:00.787 --> 17:01.486
- So, do you sing?

17:01.621 --> 17:02.453
- No, no.

17:03.590 --> 17:06.691
No, she definitely gets
her voice from her mom.

17:06.726 --> 17:08.359
- [rachael] well, come on,
I think there's a singer

17:08.395 --> 17:10.361
in there somewhere.

17:10.397 --> 17:11.863
♪ I like peanut butter ♪

17:11.898 --> 17:13.264
(rachael laughs)

17:13.299 --> 17:15.233
- I am happy to give
you lessons anytime.

17:15.268 --> 17:16.401
- Oh wow.

17:16.436 --> 17:17.535
- Rachael.
- Yeah?

17:17.570 --> 17:19.037
- We have a problem.

17:19.072 --> 17:20.938
The bake sales are way
down compared to last year

17:20.974 --> 17:24.375
and I don't know what to do.
- Well, now we just started.

17:24.411 --> 17:26.377
I'm sure things will pick up.

17:26.413 --> 17:27.712
- I don't think so.

17:27.747 --> 17:30.181
Keto's in, sugar's out.

17:30.316 --> 17:33.084
Okay, I said veggies
and bacon bites,

17:33.119 --> 17:36.187
but someone vetoed me.

17:36.322 --> 17:37.955
- How festive are bacon bites?

17:37.991 --> 17:39.524
- Unilaterally festive.

17:40.326 --> 17:42.427
- Okay, how short are we?

17:42.462 --> 17:43.561
- 2,000.

17:43.663 --> 17:44.562
- Huh?

17:44.664 --> 17:45.396
Dollars?

17:45.432 --> 17:46.397
- [ellen] yes.

17:46.499 --> 17:48.399
- For costumes?

17:48.435 --> 17:49.734
- They're authentic.

17:49.769 --> 17:52.570
- Was that from zero b.C.
Or would that be a.D.?

17:52.605 --> 17:54.906
- Maybe they turn the
sundials back a little.

17:54.941 --> 17:56.074
- They could've.

17:56.109 --> 17:57.675
- How are we gonna
sell all these sweets?

17:59.012 --> 18:00.545
- Okay, well...

18:02.015 --> 18:06.417
Oh, what's happening in that
head of yours over there?

18:07.654 --> 18:09.554
- I got a little idea.
- Yeah, what is it?

18:10.623 --> 18:12.390
- A little cookie-off.

18:12.525 --> 18:13.658
- Okay.
- Whoever sells

18:13.693 --> 18:15.526
the least cookies, buys
the other one dinner.

18:16.663 --> 18:18.429
- You are on.

18:18.465 --> 18:20.598
- Oh yeah, it is on.

18:20.633 --> 18:22.100
- Let's go.
- Let's do it.

18:23.169 --> 18:24.635
- [rachael] come on, we got it.

18:24.671 --> 18:25.903
- All right, let's do this.

18:28.308 --> 18:31.008
♪ when the snow
lay round about ♪

18:31.044 --> 18:33.811
♪ deep and crisp and even ♪

18:33.847 --> 18:36.614
♪ brightly shone the
moon that night ♪

18:36.649 --> 18:39.484
♪ though the frost was cruel ♪

18:39.519 --> 18:42.220
♪ when a poor man
came in sight ♪

18:42.322 --> 18:45.323
♪ gathering winter fuel ♪

18:45.358 --> 18:47.091
- what are you doing?

18:47.227 --> 18:48.359
- [michael] selling cookies.

18:48.394 --> 18:49.127
- No, I know you're
selling cookies,

18:49.162 --> 18:50.495
but what is it for?

18:50.530 --> 18:51.462
- The pageant.

18:52.365 --> 18:54.031
- I see you meet rachael.

18:54.067 --> 18:56.801
- Oh, yeah, no.

18:56.836 --> 18:57.635
It's not like that.

18:57.670 --> 18:58.436
It's a bet.

18:58.571 --> 18:59.704
- What is the bet?

18:59.739 --> 19:01.506
- Nothing really, just
a little whoever sells

19:01.541 --> 19:03.274
the least amount of cookies

19:03.409 --> 19:04.642
has to take the
other one to dinner.

19:04.677 --> 19:07.979
- I have some cookies to buy.

19:08.014 --> 19:09.013
- [michael] yes, you do!

19:09.048 --> 19:09.847
- From her!

19:09.883 --> 19:10.848
- [michael] what?

19:10.884 --> 19:11.682
- [emma] bye.

19:11.718 --> 19:12.517
- Yeah right.

19:12.552 --> 19:13.518
Emma?

19:13.553 --> 19:14.852
Oh, come on, that's--

19:14.888 --> 19:17.655
- oh, roasted by
your own sister.

19:17.690 --> 19:18.990
That's savage, my boy.

19:19.025 --> 19:20.525
It's savage.

19:20.560 --> 19:21.792
- Thanks, santa.

19:21.928 --> 19:23.361
- I must get back
to the north pole.

19:23.396 --> 19:27.298
You see, ever since I was a
little missing a few years ago,

19:27.433 --> 19:29.100
mrs. Claus worries about me.

19:31.104 --> 19:33.638
And michael, don't
give up on love.

19:34.741 --> 19:36.307
Just when you think
it's gone forever,

19:36.442 --> 19:37.842
love has a way of surprising you

19:37.877 --> 19:40.511
with someone you least suspect.

19:42.048 --> 19:46.717
Oh, and sophia would like
twinkie for christmas.

19:46.753 --> 19:48.186
- What's twinkie?

19:48.221 --> 19:49.720
- A puppy, michael.

19:49.756 --> 19:50.655
A puppy.

19:54.894 --> 19:56.394
- Emma, hi.
- How's it going?

19:56.429 --> 19:58.563
- Great actually.
- Good.

19:58.598 --> 20:01.199
I would like to donate 40.

20:01.234 --> 20:03.401
- Really, you're
giving it to me?

20:03.436 --> 20:04.335
- [emma] to you.

20:04.470 --> 20:05.303
- Uh-huh.
- Mm-hm.

20:06.406 --> 20:08.339
- I appreciate that.
- You're welcome.

20:08.474 --> 20:10.107
- You're gonna help me win.

20:10.143 --> 20:11.909
- That is the plan.

20:11.945 --> 20:13.578
- You could tell him
that I like italian food

20:13.613 --> 20:14.745
when he takes me out.

20:14.781 --> 20:16.347
- Italian food, got it.

20:16.482 --> 20:18.549
- Has he always been
this competitive?

20:18.585 --> 20:21.719
- Yeah, and also a
really sore loser.

20:21.821 --> 20:24.589
- Is he? (laughs)

20:24.624 --> 20:25.523
- okay.

20:27.093 --> 20:27.892
Good luck.

20:27.927 --> 20:29.060
- Thank you.

20:29.095 --> 20:29.860
- [both] bye.

20:31.764 --> 20:33.397
- Oh, goodie, goodie, goodie.

20:33.433 --> 20:36.133
It's a bake sale, how wonderful.

20:36.169 --> 20:38.336
- Dad, whatcha wearing?

20:38.438 --> 20:40.771
- Oh, this is as close
to a japanese kimono

20:40.807 --> 20:42.039
that I could get.

20:42.175 --> 20:44.141
And I'm celebrating
the emperor's birthday,

20:44.177 --> 20:46.110
and it's a national holiday.

20:46.145 --> 20:47.612
- In japan.

20:47.647 --> 20:49.614
Why are you celebrating it?

20:49.649 --> 20:51.215
- It gives me a chance to
wear something different.

20:51.351 --> 20:52.383
How much for a bag of cookies?

20:52.518 --> 20:54.619
- 50--
- no, dad.

20:54.654 --> 20:56.320
You are pre-diabetic.

20:56.356 --> 20:57.888
- I'm pre-disposed
to kick your butt

20:58.024 --> 20:59.390
unless you sell me
a bag of cookies.

20:59.525 --> 21:01.759
Otherwise I'm going over
there to your competition.

21:01.794 --> 21:03.294
- Oh, you wouldn't.

21:05.131 --> 21:07.265
All right, then, $50.

21:09.469 --> 21:10.301
- 50?

21:11.371 --> 21:12.770
I see the game you're playing.

21:12.805 --> 21:14.305
Trying to price me out, right?

21:15.842 --> 21:17.208
This is for the children.

21:19.679 --> 21:24.515
Okay, oh, oh dad, don't
look now, but donna's here.

21:24.550 --> 21:26.050
- Don't look now?

21:26.152 --> 21:28.419
I've been trying to get a
date with her for 10 years.

21:28.488 --> 21:30.321
- Dad, that's brad's mom.

21:32.325 --> 21:33.090
- Hello donna.

21:34.027 --> 21:35.293
- Carter.

21:35.395 --> 21:36.527
- You know, I was thinking

21:36.562 --> 21:40.131
that we should maybe
download a movie.

21:40.233 --> 21:41.365
Grumpy old men.

21:41.401 --> 21:43.534
- I don't do biographies.

21:43.569 --> 21:46.937
- Well, how about santa claus?

21:47.707 --> 21:50.341
- Million to one chance.

21:56.015 --> 21:57.882
- I like those odds.

21:57.917 --> 21:59.517
- Dad, she can't stand you.

21:59.552 --> 22:00.418
- Me?

22:01.721 --> 22:03.721
You're the one that told
her she was coddling brad.

22:03.756 --> 22:05.890
- I was telling the truth.

22:05.925 --> 22:07.992
- Yeah, well, it
upset her, sweetheart.

22:08.895 --> 22:10.294
Anyway, it's all a front.

22:10.430 --> 22:12.363
She can't keep her
mind off of me.

22:14.767 --> 22:15.566
- Hello.

22:15.601 --> 22:16.867
- [michael] hi.

22:16.903 --> 22:18.736
- I heard that there was
a bake sale competition.

22:18.771 --> 22:22.740
- Well there just happens to
be a bake sale competition.

22:22.775 --> 22:24.542
- What's going on over there?

22:24.577 --> 22:27.278
- And it's against them?

22:27.380 --> 22:28.879
- Oh.

22:28.915 --> 22:31.549
- Oh, it's against them.

22:31.584 --> 22:34.051
- Then I'll buy
whatever you have left.

22:34.087 --> 22:35.353
- Yes.

22:35.388 --> 22:36.887
Yes!

22:36.923 --> 22:38.923
- Does this cover it?

22:38.958 --> 22:40.358
- Wow.

22:40.460 --> 22:41.859
- I think I do.

22:47.600 --> 22:51.736
- 1500, 1600, and 1700.

22:51.771 --> 22:53.604
The winner is michael.

22:53.639 --> 22:54.705
- Yes!
- Okay,

22:54.741 --> 22:56.207
I demand a recount!

22:56.242 --> 22:59.076
- And in the true
spirit of christmas,

22:59.112 --> 23:02.747
we have enough to buy
costumes, a manger,

23:02.782 --> 23:04.315
and a glowing baby jesus.

23:05.418 --> 23:06.450
- [rachael] love that.

23:06.486 --> 23:07.351
- Ellen!

23:08.254 --> 23:09.587
Ellen!
- Wow.

23:10.957 --> 23:12.790
- I guess I'm buying dinner.

23:12.825 --> 23:14.225
- Oh, that's okay.

23:14.260 --> 23:15.626
I gotta take sophia home.

23:15.661 --> 23:17.595
- Oh, no, no no.

23:18.664 --> 23:19.697
I'm gonna take soph home

23:19.766 --> 23:22.199
and you guys are gonna
have a good night.

23:22.335 --> 23:23.467
- I won't wait up.

23:23.503 --> 23:24.435
- I'm sorry, what?

23:26.672 --> 23:27.505
- I like this one.

23:31.144 --> 23:32.042
- Good.

23:37.150 --> 23:40.651
- So, what are you up for?

23:40.686 --> 23:41.619
- Oh.

23:43.689 --> 23:45.423
I'm gonna go with lady's choice.

23:45.458 --> 23:47.291
- All right, I have
something in mind.

23:56.702 --> 23:58.636
- No, I am, I'm a total foodie.

23:58.738 --> 24:02.039
I just, japanese food, I
can't do the chopsticks.

24:02.074 --> 24:03.774
- [both] thank you.

24:03.876 --> 24:05.209
- Oh yeah, no, chopsticks?

24:05.244 --> 24:06.710
- Yeah.
- All in the thumb.

24:06.746 --> 24:08.345
- Yeah, but see I have
really small thumbs though.

24:08.381 --> 24:10.815
- I'm sorry, you have what?

24:10.917 --> 24:14.051
- Oh, I have small thumbs.

24:14.086 --> 24:15.386
Look at that, I know.

24:15.421 --> 24:16.220
I know.

24:16.255 --> 24:17.988
- They are not small.

24:18.090 --> 24:19.423
They're fine, they're great.

24:19.459 --> 24:20.357
You have great thumbs.
- Okay.

24:20.393 --> 24:22.660
You're just being nice now.

24:22.762 --> 24:24.662
- I don't really hear that.

24:24.764 --> 24:26.797
- [rachael] oh, no, why not?

24:26.899 --> 24:29.066
- My students call me
professor try hard.

24:30.102 --> 24:31.969
- What, why?

24:32.104 --> 24:33.103
- I give 'em a lot of homework.

24:33.139 --> 24:36.006
- Oh, no, really?

24:36.108 --> 24:36.907
- Yeah.

24:38.945 --> 24:40.244
Great literature is only learned

24:40.279 --> 24:42.146
by turning the pages of time.

24:43.616 --> 24:44.748
There's a lot of pages.

24:45.585 --> 24:47.685
- I definitely love to read.

24:47.787 --> 24:50.654
You will not find a
television in my bedroom.

24:51.791 --> 24:52.556
- Me too.

24:54.494 --> 24:57.228
- Okay, Sunday's are for?

24:57.263 --> 25:01.765
- Easy, mediation,
hiking, reading.

25:01.801 --> 25:04.835
- Okay, did my dad clue you in?

25:04.971 --> 25:05.669
He must've.

25:05.771 --> 25:06.570
- No.

25:07.974 --> 25:08.739
Speaking of your dad.

25:08.774 --> 25:10.241
- Mm-hm?

25:10.276 --> 25:11.108
- How long has he
been grooming you

25:11.143 --> 25:12.576
to take over the family biz?

25:12.612 --> 25:13.511
- Oh man.

25:14.814 --> 25:16.981
Seriously, as long
as I can remember.

25:18.351 --> 25:22.286
I was just a little kid and
I was elbow deep inside.

25:22.321 --> 25:24.889
I mean, I was helping
with the birthing

25:24.991 --> 25:27.958
and that was not something
that you say at a dinner date.

25:28.828 --> 25:29.593
But I liked it.

25:29.629 --> 25:31.328
I really liked it.

25:31.364 --> 25:32.263
- You liked it?

25:32.298 --> 25:34.865
- No, I mean, not that part.

25:35.001 --> 25:37.001
I mean, I like helping animals.

25:37.036 --> 25:40.070
It was really, it was
a lot of hard work,

25:40.172 --> 25:42.640
but it was really rewarding.

25:42.675 --> 25:44.608
- Now that I understand.

25:46.178 --> 25:47.144
Try that with college kids.

25:47.179 --> 25:48.546
- Oh yeah, no.

25:51.017 --> 25:54.285
- So, what's next?

25:54.320 --> 25:59.156
- Well, I mean, as soon
as we sell the clinic,

25:59.191 --> 26:00.324
my dad wants to travel.

26:00.359 --> 26:01.325
I'm just really worried
about his health.

26:01.360 --> 26:02.560
- No no no.

26:04.196 --> 26:05.629
What's next with rachael?

26:06.966 --> 26:08.098
- Music store.

26:08.200 --> 26:09.300
- Nice.

26:09.335 --> 26:11.168
- Oh yeah, my mom
was a music teacher,

26:11.203 --> 26:15.639
and I just love loved
listening to her sing

26:15.675 --> 26:17.074
and play piano.

26:17.209 --> 26:20.110
And you know, I just
thought to myself,

26:20.212 --> 26:24.348
well just why not
be around that more?

26:24.383 --> 26:25.683
- So no more animals?

26:25.718 --> 26:26.917
- Not for now.

26:27.053 --> 26:28.319
You know, maybe someday.

26:30.222 --> 26:32.356
But I'm in a place in my life

26:32.391 --> 26:34.658
that if a opportunity shows up,

26:34.694 --> 26:36.360
I gotta go for it.

26:36.395 --> 26:38.429
'cause it might not
come around again.

26:44.437 --> 26:45.336
- Are you single?

26:46.872 --> 26:49.073
- Well that was pretty forward.

26:49.108 --> 26:51.609
- But you are out on
a date with, you know.

26:52.578 --> 26:53.510
- With...

26:53.546 --> 26:54.945
- Me.

26:55.047 --> 26:56.413
- Oh.

26:56.449 --> 27:00.684
- Single dad, beautiful
daughter, I have to protect.

27:03.889 --> 27:06.724
I just can't let
anybody into our circle.

27:06.759 --> 27:08.225
- There's no one else.

27:09.295 --> 27:10.194
Just me.

27:15.101 --> 27:16.900
- Can I get you
guys anything else?

27:18.404 --> 27:20.838
- Would you mind
taking our picture?

27:20.940 --> 27:21.805
- Sure.

27:23.275 --> 27:24.008
- Is that weird?

27:24.110 --> 27:24.908
- No.
- Okay.

27:28.247 --> 27:29.713
Thank you.

27:29.749 --> 27:32.116
(both laughing)

27:32.151 --> 27:34.818
(upbeat music)

27:36.055 --> 27:38.989
♪ oh oh oh ♪

27:39.091 --> 27:40.858
♪ whoa oh oh ♪

27:40.960 --> 27:44.461
♪ oh oh oh oh ♪

27:44.497 --> 27:48.565
♪ whoa whoa whoa oh oh ♪

27:48.601 --> 27:51.602
♪ whoa whoa whoa ♪

27:51.637 --> 27:52.670
- all right.

27:54.940 --> 27:56.006
Merry christmas.

27:57.677 --> 27:59.243
Wow.

27:59.278 --> 28:02.046
Huh, hasn't seen you in what?

28:02.148 --> 28:03.313
A year.

28:03.349 --> 28:04.782
- It's a big world
out there, emma.

28:04.817 --> 28:07.885
You oughta get out of your
bubble and check it out.

28:07.920 --> 28:09.853
(emma laughs)

28:09.955 --> 28:13.023
- I moved from
new york, bradley,

28:13.125 --> 28:15.259
so I'm perfectly
fine in my bubble.

28:18.164 --> 28:19.296
What can I do for you?

28:19.331 --> 28:20.464
- What do you think?

28:20.499 --> 28:21.899
I'm here for the coffee.

28:22.001 --> 28:25.903
- Huh, for you it's 5 bucks.

28:26.005 --> 28:28.038
- 5 bucks?

28:28.174 --> 28:30.307
- Inflation is crazy.

28:30.342 --> 28:31.875
- $5 coffee, here you go.

28:31.977 --> 28:33.711
There's five, keep
the change, kid.

28:36.315 --> 28:37.147
Hey.

28:37.983 --> 28:38.949
- Yeah?

28:38.984 --> 28:40.250
- I've been looking for rachael.

28:40.352 --> 28:41.552
You haven't seen her
around, have you?

28:42.722 --> 28:44.822
Drove by the
clinic, it's closed.

28:44.857 --> 28:46.824
For sale sign out front.

28:46.859 --> 28:48.992
I drove by her house
and she's not there.

28:49.028 --> 28:50.160
Didn't move, did she?

28:51.330 --> 28:53.897
- Do you think, crazy thought,

28:54.033 --> 28:58.235
she realized you're
a opportunistic,
two-face womanizer?

28:58.370 --> 28:59.903
- (chuckles) I doubt it.

29:00.940 --> 29:03.240
Come on, it's christmas
and you know everyone.

29:03.342 --> 29:04.475
- Wouldn't have a clue.

29:08.047 --> 29:10.481
- Ugh, this coffee's terrible.

29:11.684 --> 29:13.350
Nu-uh, no.

29:13.385 --> 29:14.318
Well, tell you what,

29:14.353 --> 29:17.087
if you see her, rachael that is,

29:17.223 --> 29:21.024
just tell her the brad is back.

29:21.894 --> 29:22.659
- Loved to.

29:22.695 --> 29:23.494
- Okay.

29:23.529 --> 29:24.428
- Okay.

29:27.066 --> 29:29.399
Oh, brad, brad brad brad.
(nervously chuckles)

29:29.435 --> 29:30.367
- yes yes yes?

29:31.737 --> 29:32.603
I...

29:35.040 --> 29:35.839
- Yes?

29:37.076 --> 29:38.675
- Merry christmas.

29:38.711 --> 29:40.778
- Huh, same to you.

29:47.219 --> 29:47.951
- Oh, sorry, pal.

29:48.053 --> 29:48.719
- Sorry, pal.

29:48.754 --> 29:49.953
- Yeah, merry christmas.

29:50.055 --> 29:51.588
- [brad] merry christmas.

29:51.624 --> 29:52.422
- Hey.

29:52.458 --> 29:53.724
- [michael] hey.

29:53.759 --> 29:54.525
- What's up?

29:54.560 --> 29:55.459
- Nothing.

29:56.262 --> 29:57.561
Just here to help you close.

29:57.596 --> 29:58.762
- [emma] thanks.

29:58.798 --> 29:59.596
- How's sophia?

29:59.632 --> 30:01.165
- She's good.

30:01.267 --> 30:04.067
She is with my friend,
frances and her daughter, mae.

30:04.103 --> 30:04.968
- That's good.

30:06.272 --> 30:07.437
- Okay, you didn't just
freak out about that.

30:07.473 --> 30:08.438
I'm impressed.

30:08.474 --> 30:10.174
- Oh, I'm sure she's fine.

30:10.276 --> 30:11.241
- Yeah, she's fine.

30:14.413 --> 30:15.412
I wanted to talk--

