- Oh, um.

59:35.105 --> 59:36.705
- (gasps) congratulations.

59:36.807 --> 59:38.840
Rachael, I heard the news.

59:38.943 --> 59:40.075
Brad?

59:41.445 --> 59:43.245
Oh, it's gigantic.

59:44.181 --> 59:45.480
- I know, right?

59:46.350 --> 59:48.483
It's fake, yeah.

59:49.787 --> 59:50.552
Get this off.

59:53.157 --> 59:56.058
Please, just come off.

59:56.160 --> 59:57.225
Oh dad!
- I was just coming.

59:57.328 --> 59:58.594
- I just can't, please.
- What was going on?

59:58.629 --> 59:59.728
- Not now.

1:00:06.503 --> 1:00:07.469
- You wanna talk about it?

1:00:07.504 --> 1:00:09.271
- Dad, you're in
the ladies room.

1:00:10.641 --> 1:00:12.608
- Everybody, stay
where you are please.

1:00:12.643 --> 1:00:13.508
- Get off!

1:00:14.979 --> 1:00:15.844
- Let me see it.

1:00:17.982 --> 1:00:21.049
Oh, brad, do you love him?

1:00:21.151 --> 1:00:22.584
- Not like that!

1:00:22.686 --> 1:00:25.287
Oh dad, I made a
really big mistake.

1:00:26.190 --> 1:00:27.522
- Michael.

1:00:27.558 --> 1:00:28.457
- And I don't think there's
any way to win him back,

1:00:28.492 --> 1:00:30.626
and I can't stop thinking him.

1:00:30.661 --> 1:00:31.493
- Okay, okay.

1:00:31.528 --> 1:00:33.095
You're a smart woman, rachael.

1:00:33.197 --> 1:00:34.262
Just like your mother.

1:00:34.365 --> 1:00:35.197
And like your mother
you're gonna make

1:00:35.232 --> 1:00:36.732
the right decision, okay?

1:00:36.834 --> 1:00:39.034
You just follow your heart
and you can't go wrong.

1:00:39.069 --> 1:00:41.937
- Dad, you gotta get
out of the bathroom now.

1:00:42.039 --> 1:00:43.305
- Yeah, okay, okay.

1:00:46.844 --> 1:00:48.443
Try some dental floss around
the top of the finger.

1:00:48.545 --> 1:00:49.544
- Does it work?

1:00:49.580 --> 1:00:50.712
- Look it up.
- Okay.

1:00:57.087 --> 1:00:58.020
- Congratulations.

1:01:01.525 --> 1:01:04.059
- I need to talk to rachael.
Can I use your phone?

1:01:04.094 --> 1:01:05.494
- No.

1:01:05.529 --> 1:01:07.029
- I need to ask her something.

1:01:08.065 --> 1:01:09.665
- Come on, you have the song.

1:01:09.700 --> 1:01:10.866
You're gonna be fine.

1:01:10.901 --> 1:01:13.235
- No, dad, I have to
ask her something.

1:01:13.270 --> 1:01:14.202
- No.

1:01:14.238 --> 1:01:15.804
- [sophia] why not?

1:01:15.906 --> 1:01:16.905
- Because I said so.

1:01:18.442 --> 1:01:20.308
- You are acting a kid.

1:01:20.411 --> 1:01:24.379
- You don't need rachael
to sing better, all right?

1:01:25.716 --> 1:01:27.949
Can we just stop talking about
this? Please, I wanna eat.

1:01:28.052 --> 1:01:29.184
- Okay, you okay?

1:01:32.589 --> 1:01:33.655
- Yeah, why?

1:01:34.925 --> 1:01:37.592
- Okay, say it, don't spray it.

1:01:43.600 --> 1:01:45.000
- How you holding up?

1:01:45.102 --> 1:01:46.835
- Not working, not working.

1:01:50.274 --> 1:01:51.540
- You finally get what you want,

1:01:51.575 --> 1:01:53.275
and now you don't know
if you want it anymore.

1:01:53.310 --> 1:01:56.545
- I know that I want
this thing off my finger.

1:01:56.580 --> 1:01:58.146
- You call michael?

1:01:58.248 --> 1:01:59.214
- No.

1:02:00.951 --> 1:02:03.385
Dad, I don't know
what I'm gonna say.

1:02:05.789 --> 1:02:08.724
- Sounds to me like you've
already made up your mind.

1:02:08.759 --> 1:02:11.593
- Dad, it just happened so fast.

1:02:11.628 --> 1:02:12.561
- Love's a bullet, baby.

1:02:12.596 --> 1:02:14.396
Don't let it take you down.

1:02:17.167 --> 1:02:19.267
- Dad, I really hurt him.

1:02:23.307 --> 1:02:24.272
- He'll understand.

1:02:25.943 --> 1:02:29.578
- And what if he doesn't?

1:02:36.019 --> 1:02:36.885
- Do something.

1:02:38.155 --> 1:02:39.254
Tell him how you feel.

1:02:41.358 --> 1:02:42.290
Yeah?

1:02:43.794 --> 1:02:46.294
You're not gonna get him back
standing here talking to me.

1:02:50.334 --> 1:02:51.733
This...

1:02:51.835 --> 1:02:53.401
- Yeah.

1:02:53.504 --> 1:02:57.606
- Oof, try some coconut
oil on that, all right?

1:02:57.641 --> 1:02:59.007
- Coconut, okay.

1:03:01.545 --> 1:03:03.211
- Who loves you?

1:03:03.313 --> 1:03:04.146
- You.

1:03:05.549 --> 1:03:06.448
- I do.

1:03:19.363 --> 1:03:22.464
(soft somber music)

1:03:27.838 --> 1:03:28.870
- you okay?

1:03:33.377 --> 1:03:34.476
- I'm fine.

1:03:39.416 --> 1:03:41.817
- Do you remember
when we were kids

1:03:41.852 --> 1:03:44.820
how I use to break out in hives
every time we went camping?

1:03:46.256 --> 1:03:48.657
Mom and dad could not figure
out what I was allergic to

1:03:48.692 --> 1:03:50.692
and we had to leave the
campground every year

1:03:50.727 --> 1:03:51.960
and go get a hotel.

1:03:54.731 --> 1:03:57.332
About 10 years ago I
figured out what it was.

1:03:59.736 --> 1:04:00.669
Stress.

1:04:04.408 --> 1:04:06.441
And I'm sorry that
I wasn't there.

1:04:06.543 --> 1:04:08.410
I know when she died, that
was really hard on you,

1:04:08.445 --> 1:04:09.244
and I should've--

1:04:09.279 --> 1:04:10.812
- no no.

1:04:10.914 --> 1:04:12.681
No, look at me.

1:04:13.584 --> 1:04:14.516
I'm happy.

1:04:18.255 --> 1:04:19.087
Come here.

1:04:20.591 --> 1:04:21.656
I love you.

1:04:21.758 --> 1:04:22.691
- I love you, too.

1:04:25.062 --> 1:04:27.863
I forgot to set the
alarm at the cafe.

1:04:27.898 --> 1:04:29.397
So I'm gonna turn that off.

1:04:29.433 --> 1:04:30.765
- No no, I'll get it.

1:04:30.801 --> 1:04:31.566
- No.

1:04:31.602 --> 1:04:32.868
- Yeah yeah, listen.

1:04:32.903 --> 1:04:34.703
Please, go chill with sophie.

1:04:35.906 --> 1:04:38.006
The pageant's coming
up and she's like...

1:04:39.643 --> 1:04:41.243
She's says I'm
hovering over here.

1:04:41.278 --> 1:04:42.744
I make her nervous.

1:04:42.779 --> 1:04:43.678
- She said that?

1:04:43.780 --> 1:04:45.046
- Mm-hm.

1:04:45.082 --> 1:04:45.947
- Yeah, okay.

1:04:47.084 --> 1:04:48.416
- All right, cool,
I'll see you there.

1:04:48.452 --> 1:04:49.918
- Mm-hm, I'll see you.

1:04:49.953 --> 1:04:50.752
- [michael] bye.

1:04:50.787 --> 1:04:51.720
- Bye.

1:04:52.522 --> 1:04:53.922
St a little left.

1:04:53.957 --> 1:04:54.890
- [ellen] I got it!

1:04:54.925 --> 1:04:56.258
- Just a little bit more right.

1:04:56.293 --> 1:04:57.525
- I got it.

1:04:57.628 --> 1:04:59.127
- [pastor] just a
little bit right.

1:04:59.162 --> 1:05:01.263
(glass shatters)
- don't got it.

1:05:01.298 --> 1:05:02.230
I'll fix it.

1:05:03.600 --> 1:05:07.202
- It looks like maybe you
could use a little help.

1:05:07.304 --> 1:05:09.237
- I think you could more than I.

1:05:10.507 --> 1:05:15.043
- Yeah, I think I'm just gonna
cut the whole finger off.

1:05:15.145 --> 1:05:17.112
- I have shears in the
green shed if you wanna.

1:05:17.147 --> 1:05:18.113
- Oh okay.

1:05:19.816 --> 1:05:22.784
Look, can I ask you a question?

1:05:22.819 --> 1:05:24.452
- Always go with your instinct.

1:05:26.356 --> 1:05:28.056
- My dad said the
extra same thing.

1:05:28.158 --> 1:05:28.990
- Wise man.

1:05:30.327 --> 1:05:32.227
Look, whatever you decide,
just consider the fact

1:05:32.329 --> 1:05:35.497
that there are three people
affected by this decision.

1:05:35.532 --> 1:05:36.498
- Three?

1:05:36.533 --> 1:05:38.867
- You, michael, and brad.

1:05:38.969 --> 1:05:40.302
- [rachael] brad.

1:05:40.337 --> 1:05:41.469
- You may not wanna be with him,

1:05:41.505 --> 1:05:43.271
but you have to consider
his feelings too.

1:05:46.843 --> 1:05:51.913
- Yeah, and now on the
other hand, michael.

1:05:53.050 --> 1:05:56.418
Yeah, I don't think that
he's gonna forgive me.

1:05:56.520 --> 1:05:59.020
I mean, I lied to him.

1:05:59.056 --> 1:06:00.789
- Sounds like a pickle.

1:06:00.824 --> 1:06:03.692
- Pickle, mrs. Pickle,
she's so cute, right?

1:06:04.695 --> 1:06:05.393
- Who?

1:06:05.495 --> 1:06:07.495
- The dog, no?

1:06:07.531 --> 1:06:08.463
Nevermind.

1:06:10.567 --> 1:06:12.133
So, what do I do?

1:06:13.870 --> 1:06:16.771
- First, we start by being
honest with yourself.

1:06:16.873 --> 1:06:18.640
And then you go be
honest with them.

1:06:20.077 --> 1:06:24.946
- And what happens if
they both leave me?

1:06:26.049 --> 1:06:28.016
- Then neither one of
them was right for you.

1:06:28.051 --> 1:06:29.517
God works in mysterious ways.

1:06:31.054 --> 1:06:32.020
- Yes.

1:06:33.423 --> 1:06:35.657
You're good, you're good.

1:06:36.660 --> 1:06:38.793
- Actually I need some
refreshments picked up

1:06:38.895 --> 1:06:40.095
from brad's house.

1:06:40.197 --> 1:06:42.664
Might be a good time
to go clear the air?

1:06:45.435 --> 1:06:46.368
- Yeah.

1:06:47.904 --> 1:06:48.803
Okay.

1:06:50.874 --> 1:06:53.541
I really wish that I could
get this ring off my.

1:07:03.120 --> 1:07:04.219
- Mysterious ways.

1:07:19.403 --> 1:07:22.103
(doorbell rings)

1:07:25.776 --> 1:07:26.608
- [brad] rachael?

1:07:26.643 --> 1:07:28.143
- Hello brad.

1:07:28.245 --> 1:07:29.010
- [brad] what are
you doing here?

1:07:29.112 --> 1:07:30.145
- Okay, two things.

1:07:30.247 --> 1:07:32.113
One, I gotta pick
up the cookies.

1:07:32.149 --> 1:07:34.182
And number two, I
really wanna talk.

1:07:34.284 --> 1:07:36.618
- Yeah, well, the
last batch is cooking.

1:07:36.653 --> 1:07:37.719
Gingerbread men.

1:07:37.754 --> 1:07:39.320
- Oh, you made gingerbread men?

1:07:39.423 --> 1:07:40.455
- I did.

1:07:40.490 --> 1:07:41.589
And one of them attacked me

1:07:41.625 --> 1:07:43.758
and mrs. Pickles
barely saved my life.

1:07:43.794 --> 1:07:45.093
She gassed them out.

1:07:45.128 --> 1:07:46.461
- Oh stop.

1:07:46.496 --> 1:07:48.763
- Brad, who's at the door?

1:07:48.799 --> 1:07:50.598
Oh, rachael.

1:07:50.634 --> 1:07:51.699
- Hi donna.

1:07:51.802 --> 1:07:52.600
- Hi.

1:07:53.970 --> 1:07:56.938
Is dennis going to
the show tonight?

1:07:56.973 --> 1:07:58.440
- I suppose.

1:07:58.475 --> 1:08:00.742
- Well, I mean, not that I care.

1:08:00.777 --> 1:08:01.810
- Of course not.

1:08:01.845 --> 1:08:02.644
- Who said I did?

1:08:02.679 --> 1:08:03.945
- No one.

1:08:03.980 --> 1:08:05.647
- Well, there's a formal event,

1:08:05.682 --> 1:08:07.482
and I should get ready.

1:08:07.517 --> 1:08:09.484
I'd like to look my best,

1:08:09.519 --> 1:08:11.453
but not for anyone special.

1:08:11.488 --> 1:08:12.921
- Who would it be for?

1:08:12.956 --> 1:08:13.988
- No one.
- Yeah.

1:08:18.795 --> 1:08:20.128
- Rachael, sweetie.

1:08:20.163 --> 1:08:21.563
- Yeah, look, listen.

1:08:21.665 --> 1:08:24.766
Come here, I really wanna
talk to you about this

1:08:24.801 --> 1:08:27.902
because this has really been
weighing really heavy on me.

1:08:29.172 --> 1:08:33.942
And well, I can't marry you.

1:08:34.978 --> 1:08:38.113
- Oh, well why not?

1:08:38.148 --> 1:08:39.781
- I don't love you.

1:08:41.017 --> 1:08:43.218
- Okay, so then you hate me.

1:08:43.320 --> 1:08:47.088
- No, I don't hate you.

1:08:48.191 --> 1:08:49.424
We're good friends

1:08:49.526 --> 1:08:53.161
and we're really good
at being good friends.

1:08:53.196 --> 1:08:56.531
Just with no commitment.

1:08:56.566 --> 1:08:59.434
I mean, there's a
lot of love here.

1:08:59.536 --> 1:09:03.571
I'm just not in love with you.

1:09:03.673 --> 1:09:08.409
And, well, I finally
know the difference.

1:09:08.512 --> 1:09:10.445
- I get it, I do.

1:09:10.547 --> 1:09:14.649
- Look, despite everything
that we've been through,

1:09:15.752 --> 1:09:17.552
I really do think
you are gonna make

1:09:17.587 --> 1:09:19.821
an amazing husband some day.

1:09:20.724 --> 1:09:22.090
- No, no, I'm not.

1:09:22.192 --> 1:09:23.358
- [rachael] why?

1:09:23.393 --> 1:09:25.593
- You can keep the
ring, it's a fake.

1:09:25.695 --> 1:09:27.162
- Yeah, I know.

1:09:27.197 --> 1:09:28.997
(brad sighs)

1:09:29.032 --> 1:09:33.001
- and I wanted to marry
you because I'm broke.

1:09:33.036 --> 1:09:34.068
- [both women] what?

1:09:39.075 --> 1:09:42.544
- I made a bad business
investment with tony bruno.

1:09:44.881 --> 1:09:48.550
I borrowed $200,000 and if
I don't get it back to him,

1:09:48.585 --> 1:09:50.552
this will be my last christmas.

1:09:50.587 --> 1:09:52.554
- And why didn't you tell me?

1:09:52.589 --> 1:09:54.556
- Mom, because you're
always hovering around me.

1:09:54.591 --> 1:09:56.024
I mean, you're
always paying things.

1:09:56.059 --> 1:09:57.825
I need some space.

1:09:57.928 --> 1:10:01.062
The music festival was
gonna be my way out.

1:10:01.097 --> 1:10:02.764
But it flopped.

1:10:02.799 --> 1:10:04.632
And the artist
didn't even show up,

1:10:04.734 --> 1:10:07.569
and I had to refund
everybody's tickets.

1:10:10.473 --> 1:10:12.907
I'm sorry for everything.

1:10:12.943 --> 1:10:14.242
- I know, I know.

1:10:20.450 --> 1:10:21.649
(brad sighs)

1:10:21.751 --> 1:10:23.518
- all right, I'm gonna
go get the cookies.

1:10:23.620 --> 1:10:24.419
- Okay.

1:10:29.626 --> 1:10:33.861
- Well, I guess this is
the eve for coming clean.

1:10:34.931 --> 1:10:39.734
So, tell your father
to save a seat for moi.

1:10:47.310 --> 1:10:48.042
- Okay.

1:10:49.980 --> 1:10:51.546
- Excuse me.

1:10:51.648 --> 1:10:54.549
- [michael] sorry, we're
closed for christmas eve.

1:10:54.651 --> 1:10:57.085
- No, I'm not here for the food.

1:10:57.120 --> 1:10:59.320
Dennis, we meet the other night.

1:11:00.490 --> 1:11:01.256
- How are you, dennis?

1:11:01.291 --> 1:11:02.056
- How are you, man?

1:11:02.158 --> 1:11:03.558
- Good.

1:11:03.660 --> 1:11:06.261
- Do you have a second that
I could maybe talk to you?

1:11:06.296 --> 1:11:07.395
- Sure, have a seat.

1:11:07.497 --> 1:11:08.329
- Okay.

1:11:09.666 --> 1:11:10.531
Just take a minute.

1:11:10.634 --> 1:11:15.637
- [michael] sure.

1:11:17.874 --> 1:11:21.009
- I'm sure rachael's talked
to you about her mom.

1:11:21.044 --> 1:11:22.377
- Mm-hm.

1:11:22.479 --> 1:11:27.482
- Elizabeth, spectacular
woman, outstanding.

1:11:28.184 --> 1:11:29.250
Every much like rachael.

1:11:30.687 --> 1:11:34.722
Independent and resilient
and thick-headed, yeah?

1:11:34.824 --> 1:11:36.958
(laughs)

1:11:39.729 --> 1:11:43.431
when we met, she was engaged

1:11:43.533 --> 1:11:47.101
to the high school
quarterback star.

1:11:47.203 --> 1:11:50.371
He had a giant scholarship
to yale, right?

1:11:50.407 --> 1:11:52.974
I was this scrawny kid.

1:11:53.009 --> 1:11:54.876
I had no business picking
up the homecoming queen.

1:11:54.911 --> 1:11:56.978
Much less, bobby's
finance, right?

1:11:58.048 --> 1:12:01.816
But man, I was driven, you know?

1:12:03.053 --> 1:12:05.987
She really make me feel alive.

1:12:07.357 --> 1:12:09.324
I heard no a lot more
than I heard yes,

1:12:09.359 --> 1:12:14.162
but being the tenacious
son-of-a-gun that I am,

1:12:14.197 --> 1:12:19.300
I persisted and eventually I
stole her from bobby, right?

1:12:22.772 --> 1:12:23.705
- Dennis.

1:12:27.911 --> 1:12:29.310
I get it.

1:12:29.412 --> 1:12:30.912
- Okay.

1:12:30.947 --> 1:12:33.481
- But she didn't
tell me about brad,

1:12:33.583 --> 1:12:35.016
and I have to protect sophia.

1:12:36.453 --> 1:12:38.820
I've only dated one woman
since sophia's mom passed.

1:12:38.922 --> 1:12:43.558
And when things went
wrong and affected her,

1:12:44.794 --> 1:12:47.195
I just have to be really
careful right now.

1:12:47.230 --> 1:12:49.864
That's where I'm at, you
understand that, right?

1:12:51.634 --> 1:12:53.668
- Yes, and I commend
you for that.

1:12:53.770 --> 1:12:55.670
I mean, that was very honorable.

1:12:55.772 --> 1:12:59.574
But michael, everybody
make mistakes.

1:13:00.410 --> 1:13:03.745
She thought brad was long gone.

1:13:03.780 --> 1:13:05.913
And speaking for myself,

1:13:05.949 --> 1:13:08.883
I never thought he was in the
running in the first place.

1:13:10.120 --> 1:13:11.652
All right, I know I'm rambling.

1:13:11.755 --> 1:13:13.187
Dennis, come on,
get to the point.

1:13:13.289 --> 1:13:17.925
Okay, the real test of
love is forgiveness.

1:13:20.263 --> 1:13:22.263
Can you forgive her
for what she did?

1:13:22.298 --> 1:13:24.866
Because I've never seen her
act the way she's acting

1:13:24.968 --> 1:13:26.234
around another man.

1:13:26.269 --> 1:13:29.203
And michael, that
makes you special.

1:13:32.308 --> 1:13:33.474
That's my whole spiel.

1:13:37.147 --> 1:13:38.479
(michael sighs)

1:13:38.515 --> 1:13:39.981
- and I appreciate you.

1:13:40.016 --> 1:13:43.317
- All right, thanks for taking
a minute to listen to me.

1:13:44.120 --> 1:13:45.253
- Merry christmas.

1:13:45.288 --> 1:13:46.254
- Merry christmas.

1:13:58.968 --> 1:14:01.636
(michael sighs)

1:14:09.879 --> 1:14:13.114
(church bell ringing)

1:14:23.893 --> 1:14:25.393
- [emma] you look great.

1:14:25.428 --> 1:14:26.327
